{"uuid": "78201ba2-bba6-4c8a-a477-ee196e2be8e9", "id": 7880, "date": "2019-03-21T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2019-03-21T12:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=7880"}, "modified": "2020-12-09T05:30:36", "modified_gmt": "2020-12-09T13:30:36", "slug": "matr-dave-edmunds-and-bruce-springsteen-lets-talk-about-us", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/03/21/matr-dave-edmunds-and-bruce-springsteen-lets-talk-about-us/", "title": {"rendered": "MatR: Dave Edmunds and Bruce Springsteen, Let&#8217;s Talk About Us"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>&#8220;Let&#8217;s Talk About Us&#8221; isn&#8217;t one of Jerry Lee Lewis&#8217; most well-known songs (released as a single in 1959, it never charted), but it&#8217;s certainly one of his most direct.</p>\n<p>Even for Lewis, known for his suggestive lyrics, &#8220;Let&#8217;s Talk About Us&#8221; is a remarkably direct song for its time. Jerry Lee plays an impatient suitor telling his girl that he&#8217;s waited long enough: it&#8217;s sexy time.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Let&#039;s Talk About Us\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/fzppE4nXH7s?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>It may not make it to a fan&#8217;s sign request let alone get selected, but Bruce did cover it once&#8211;on stage in 1982 with Dave Edmunds (who charted that year with his cover of &#8220;From Small Things (Big Things One Day Come)&#8221;) at the short-lived but legendary Big Man&#8217;s West in Red Bank.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s that performance (with Bruce playing a supporting role on this one), from September 18, 1982.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Bruce Springsteen &amp; Dave 